                            <comment id="12884826" author="streamy" created="Fri, 2 Jul 2010 22:13:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should definitely do #1.  +1 on configurable like ZK and also pre-configured HDFS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think #2 could be interesting but I&apos;m not sure in which contexts it makes sense.  Single node, yeah.  But if you have a cluster it seems like you benefit from multiple JVMs.  Is it really that much more simple to launch a cluster of one process per server vs two or three?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are there some benefits I&apos;m not thinking about?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12884840" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 2 Jul 2010 22:49:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;About #2, it&apos;s just a proposal to counter the &quot;too many components&quot; argument.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12884853" author="streamy" created="Fri, 2 Jul 2010 23:25:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, I do think it&apos;s an interesting idea.  Not trying to just shoot it down, trying to think if there are benefits out there over approach #1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902221" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 00:45:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s punt to 0.92.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902263" author="streamy" created="Wed, 25 Aug 2010 01:19:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d really like to see #1 happen for 0.90.  Someone did take ownership of this at some point, need to dig through my notes &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047530" author="stack" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 22:45:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving out of 0.92.0. Pull it back in if you think different.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14490643" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2015 00:46:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lovely idea but we&apos;ve been talking about it for more than 5 years&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
